'#': Use it for prefix comments iun the code
'nameUART,packet_to_send': nameUART - Specify the COM port (include UART in comPort name) to match the COM you intend to use, Sends packet ofter the ','
'RELAY,number,on/off': For Example, if {number} = 1 & {on/off} = ON then RELAY,1,1
'CHKMSGBYTE,test_name,msb,lsb,h_bit,l_bi: Gets specific RX data from the mainUART COM
'SCP{scope}MEAS': For Example, scope 1 use SCP1MEAS, save measurements from the scope, use the command before SCP{scope}M{meas_number}
'SCP{scope}M{meas_number}',,,: For Example, scope 1 meas number 2 use SCP1M2, return second meas from the scope use the function after SCP{scope}MEAS
'SCP{scope}LDSU,setup_path': Load setup to scope from file setup_path (.agilent)
'SCP{scope}SING,': Change scope Run Control to Signal
'SCP{scope}STOP,': Change scope Run Control to STOP
'SCP{scope}SVSC,': Screenshot the scope and save it in save location of the .script
